10:
Oh, Alk! You came at just the right
time!
14:
Hey there, Ellya. What's up? On your
way back from the Kaleidoscope?
Or are you heading there now?
18:
Neither! There's actually something I
wanted to ask you!
22:
How do you tell someone how you
really feel about them?
30:
Oh, I see. Your friend asked you for
relationship advice.
34:
Yep. I've already told her I think she
should just be honest with him, but
she's too shy to say it!
37:
No way! I told you I'm too much of a
wimp to do that! That's why I'm here
asking for advice.
39:
Hmm... Well, how about giving them
chocolates? Valentine's Fest IS
coming up soon, after all.
43:
Huh? What does giving chocolates
have to do with confessing your
love? I don't get it.
48:
Am I misremembering or
something? I could have sworn
that's what people did during
Valentine's Fest...
52:
Well, anyway, just think of it like
you're giving someone a present to
show them your true feelings.
56:
I suppose that might make it easier
to confess! The atmosphere of the
festival is a plus too!
59:
Y-yeah... I might be able to give that
a try! ...Maybe.
62: All right! That settles it, then!
69:
Welcome to Alk's special lesson on
how to make your own Valentine's
chocolate! Here we go! How about
we show our teacher here some
gratitude?
75:
Is it just me or are there way more
people than before?
Also, what's with the outfit change,
Ellya?
79:
Hehe. I figured I might as well make
a big event out of this! The outfit is
for advertising purposesâ€”doesn't it
look great on me?
85:
I mean, I won't deny that it suits you,
but... Why did you go and turn this
into a whole event?!
90:
When you suggested making
chocolates, I got all these ideas in
my head, that's all! This could make
everyone way more hyped for the
festival!
94:
I guess so... Thankfully, I think we
have enough ingredients to make
chocolates for a group this size.
98:
Ahem. Okay, let's get started. First,
chop up your chocolate into fine
piecesâ€”store-bought is fine, of
course. To do that, you'll want to firstâ€”
101:
Hey... Don't you think Ellya and Alk
are standing a little close to each
other? You think they might be
dating?
103:
Nah... You're way off there. That's just
how Ellya isâ€”a real airhead... Plus,
she doesn't get the concept of
personal space.
105:
Yep. Tons of guys fall for her 'cause
of that. I wonder if the same will
happen to Alk.
108:
Why is everyone so interested in my
love life...
115: You know, I'm super curious now too.
117:
Hey Ellya, you and Alk definitely
aren't dating, right? If that's the
case, what kind of guys are you
into? We wanna know!
120:
H-huh? I never really thought about
it...
123:
I guess... I'd like someone who has
the same vision as meâ€”someone
who's got their eyes on the same
destination!
127:
Then, they need to be tough. Super
tough. Like, enough to go into the
Depths with me.
131:
Finally, I guess we have to be on the
same page? We need to be in sync
mentally, you know? I have to know
what they're gonna do next!
134:
Wait a minute. Aren't you just
describing your ideal party
member?! This is LOVE, Ellya, not the
Kaleidoscope!
137:
What's the difference? Either way,
you're putting your life in someone
else's hands!
140:
Huh? It doesn't have to be that
intense, you know! We're talking
about love here!
142:
Yeah! Love is more like... when you
get a big stupid grin on your face
thinking about someone! Or when
you're sad when they're not around!
149:
It's no use, she's not getting it at
all!
Haven't you ever been in love?
159:
I mean... What IS love? I don't even
really understand it...
163:
What's with that reaction? Did I say
something weird?
166:
Not exactly weird... It's just...
Love isn't something you have to
understand. It just happens!
168:
All I know is, I definitely picked the
wrong person to ask for love advice.
175:
It's okay, forget about Ellyaâ€”she's
hopeless when it comes to this stuff.
I wanna know more about YOU,
Cathy. What's this I hear about a
love triangle?
179:
Hey! What do you mean, I'm
hopeless?
183:
So, uh... How about that cooking
lesson?
190:
And we're done! Of course, you don't
even have to pour the chocolate
into a moldâ€”you can feel free to mix
it into cake as well!
195:
Doesn't mine look awesome? With a
delicious-looking chocolate like this,
he's sure to fall head over heels for
me!
197: I think I can finally confess with this!
203:
Don't think you're getting off the
hook that easily, Ellya! You need to
give chocolate to someone too!
206:
R-right. I'm sure I'll find someone I
like at some point... Eventually.
209:
Hey, Alk. If Ellya does end up getting
a crush on someone, make sure to
help her out, okay?
218:
Ditto on that request. I think I'll need
all the help I can get!
